# Dairo + Go (net/http)

This starter was scaffolded by `dairo init go-http`. It is a `net/http` server
with an outbound send route and an inbound webhook handler that verifies delivery
signatures.

## Files

- `main.go` — the server: `POST /api/dairo/send` and the inbound webhook handler
  at `POST {{inbox_route}}`.
- `go.mod` — module stub requiring `github.com/dairo-app/dairo-go`.

## 1. Set your API key

```sh
cp .env.example .env
export DAIRO_API_KEY=dairo_...
export DAIRO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
```

The Go SDK reads the key from the value you pass to `dairo.NewClient(...)`; this
template passes `os.Getenv("DAIRO_API_KEY")`.

## 2. Install and run

```sh
{{install_cmd}}
go run .
```

## 3. Register the webhook

```sh
dairo webhook create --url https://<your-tunnel>{{inbox_route}} --event {{webhook_event}}
```

Local development:

```sh
dairo listen --forward-to http://localhost:8080{{inbox_route}}
```

## Raw body gotcha

`io.ReadAll(r.Body)` reads the **raw bytes**. `dairo.VerifyWebhookRequest` checks
the signature against those bytes using the `X-Dairo-Signature` /
`X-Dairo-Timestamp` headers; verify before `json.Unmarshal`.
